5cb7c7ea192e"],

Cell["\<\
An anomalous  (or \[OpenCurlyQuote]2\[CloseCurlyQuote]) Nambu index is \
introduced whenever a homogeneous pair of second-quantization operators is \
found, consistently with the definition of the one-body Gorkov propagators \
(cf. Som\[AGrave] et al, 2011). In Bogoliubov diagrams, involute \
single-particle indices do appear, since at least an anomalous contraction of \
external single-particle indices is present. In this case, involute \
single-particle indices are mapped into negative natural numbers. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.888317299620916*^9, 3.8883174034984384`*^9}, {
  3.888317685104419*^9, 3.888317943793604*^9}, {3.919021006380827*^9, 
  3.9190210250478587`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7681964c-6713-46b8-b744-\
edde654e7eb2"],

